HEADWORD: Hidrosis
<hw>Hi*dro"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written
also, but incorrectly, <asp>idrosis</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ to sweat, <?/ sweat.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Excretion of sweat; perspiration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Excessive perspiration; also, any
skin disease characterized by abnormal perspiration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hidrotic</ent>⟦br⟧
